main event: Seven white lights were observed near Waynesboro, Pennsylvania on September 20, 1968.
interesting points: The lights were about the size of jet aircraft and were observed at an elevation of around 20 degrees.
The lights traveled from southeast to northwest and disappeared over the horizon in about 10-15 minutes.
The observer did not hear any noise from the lights and decided they were not high-flying aircraft because no vapor trail was visible.
The angular velocity of the lights was fairly rapid.
The witness was located at Ft. Detrick, Maryland.
